description:
"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

Monologue: Obama's 7th and last appearance on Daily Show in it's current incarnation.  Obama believes that the government is working better now than any time in our history. Kennedy is not so sure.

Tonight's panel: KATHERINE MANGU-WARD, SAM MORRIL, and TOM SHILLUE. Clinton is trailing behind 3 Republican contenders in some swing states. Recent polls show Donald Trump's Unfavorable rating highest among any presidential candidate. (Polls in CO, IA, & VA.) They also discuss Trump recently giving out Lindsay Graham's phone number on stage.

The panel returns to talk about Obama's Daily Show interview. Specifically the part where he says the IRS scandal is no big deal.

CHARLIE LeDUFF is here via satellite to talk about his recent "The Americans" special on the KKK. He spends time with a few Klan members. They are predictably stupid.

Our panel returns. First topic - being a father makes you fat. Seasonable creep already starting. Halloween in July. Ashley Madison hacked.

JEFF FLOCK is here via car to talk about hacking Jeep Charokees.

Nightcap: De Blasio VS Uber.
